      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 45 初六</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 45 初六</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>初六：有孚不終，乃亂乃萃，若號一握為笑，勿恤，往无咎。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The first SIX, divided, shows its subject with a sincere desire (for union), but unable to carry it out, so that disorder is brought into the sphere of his union. If he cry out (for help to his proper correlate), all at once (his tears) will give place to smiles. He need not mind (the temporary difficulty); as he goes forward, there will be no error.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
